Unirecfilter README

Goal:	This NEMEA module selects records according to parameters
	in filter and sends only fields specified in output template.
	
Input Intreface: UniRec format specified with -I parameter.
Output Interface: UniRec format specified with -O parameter.

Parameters:
   -I TMPLT	Specify UniRec template expected on the input interface.
   -O TMPLT	Specify UniRec template expected on the output interface.
   -F FILR	Specify filter.
   -f FILE	Read template and filter from FILE.
   -c N		Quit after N records are received.

Notes: 	Filter contains expressions like (<=, ==, &&, ...).
       	Format of the file is TMPLT:FLTR or only :FLTR on the first line.
       	When is -O flag missing, template from input is used on output.

Usage: 	./unirecfilter -i IFC_SPEC -I TMPLT [-O TMPLT] [-F FLTR]
	./unirecfilter -i IFC_SPEC -I TMPLT [-f FILE]

